.TH GETMINOR 9 "$Date: 2005/03/12 13:06:43 $" "$Name:  $ STREAMS"
.SH "NAME"
.B getminor
\- get the minor device number for a device.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
.B #include <sys/streams.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/ddi.h>
.HP 8
.BI "unsigned char " retval " = getminor(dev_t " dev );
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
.TP
.I dev
the device number from which to extract the minor device number.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.BR getminor ()
returns the minor device number associated with the
.B dev_t
.IR dev .
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
.PP
Always returns the minor device number.
.SH "ERRORS"
.PP
Always succeeds.
.SH "CAVEATS"
.PP
.BR getminor ()
simply invokes the kernel macro
.BR MINOR ().
.SH "VERSIONS"
.PP
